\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Cumulative returns (log scale) for PRISM No-Lev, equal-weight, and SPY, all vol-targeted to 15\% with leverage capped at 1$\times $. The comparison is fair: all three strategies face identical risk budgets. PRISM compounds wealth at a substantially higher rate while absorbing dramatically smaller drawdowns.}}{8}{figure.caption.13}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:cumret}{{8}{8}{Cumulative returns (log scale) for PRISM No-Lev, equal-weight, and SPY, all vol-targeted to 15\% with leverage capped at 1$\times $. The comparison is fair: all three strategies face identical risk budgets. PRISM compounds wealth at a substantially higher rate while absorbing dramatically smaller drawdowns}{figure.caption.13}{}}
