\newlabel{fig:drawdowns}{{9}{8}{Drawdown profiles for PRISM No-Lev (top), EW No-Lev (middle), and SPY No-Lev (bottom). PRISM's worst drawdown ($-9.3\%$) is a fraction of EW ($-21.9\%$) and SPY ($-27.3\%$), demonstrating superior downside protection from the confidence-gated allocation}{figure.caption.14}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10}{\ignorespaces Rolling 26-week annualised volatility for PRISM No-Lev, PRISM Raw, EW, and SPY. The no-leverage vol-targeting (dashed red line at 15\%) keeps PRISM within the target budget during calm markets and scales back during crises---it never adds leverage. SPY exhibits persistent over-target vol during stress events.}}{8}{figure.caption.15}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:rollvol}{{10}{8}{Rolling 26-week annualised volatility for PRISM No-Lev, PRISM Raw, EW, and SPY. The no-leverage vol-targeting (dashed red line at 15\%) keeps PRISM within the target budget during calm markets and scales back during crises---it never adds leverage. SPY exhibits persistent over-target vol during stress events}{figure.caption.15}{}}
